          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>IDEA High Cost Pool Funding Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Individuals with Disabilities Act to establish additional grants for the purpose of assisting&nbsp;states in addressing the needs of high-need children with disabilities. The bill establishes limitations on grant amounts and how grant funds may be used.</p> <p>To be eligible to receive such a grant, a state shall: (1) provide matching funds equal to at least 25% of the grant amount; and (2) provide any information that the Department of Education may require, as specified by the bill.</p> <p>A state may request a waiver of certain grant requirements that are incompatible with aspects of the state's governmental structure.</p>]]></text>
